# Stage 2 -- GE2E learned embeddings (summary)

Open-set: 44 held-out eval users (never trained on), reference/query halves = Stage-1 splits/seeds.  Fingerprint = mean of learned game vectors, matched-C10 retrieval (chance 0.100).  Baseline 'both' is rebuilt on the SAME 44 users.

**Caveat**: eval pool is 44 users vs Stage-1's 164, so full-pool chance differs; matched-C10 is the apples-to-apples comparison.

## matched-C10 top-1 @N=50 (mean±sd over 2 seeds)

| model | all-users | within-class | within-archetype |
|-------|----------:|-------------:|-----------------:|
| baseline 'both' (44u) | 0.823±0.000 | 0.842±0.000 | 0.500±0.000 |
| GE2E (a) embed | 0.974±0.026 | 0.968±0.010 | 0.750±0.050 |
| GE2E (b) LSA | 0.958±0.010 | 0.948±0.022 | 0.850±0.050 |
| GE2E (b)+adversarial | 0.954±0.008 | 0.928±0.005 | 0.700±0.100 |

## Deck-recognition gap (identical pilots; all vs same-archetype distractors)

| model | distractors=all | distractors=archetype | gap |
|-------|----------------:|----------------------:|----:|
| baseline 'both' | 0.983 | 0.500 | 0.483 |
| GE2E (a) embed | 0.995 | 0.750 | 0.245 |
| GE2E (b) LSA | 0.992 | 0.850 | 0.142 |
| GE2E (b)+adv | 0.991 | 0.700 | 0.291 |

## Answers

1. **Beat baseline within-archetype?** baseline 'both' = 0.500; best learned = 0.850. -> YES (matched-C10 top-1 @N=50).
2. **Adversarial shrinks the deck gap?** variant (a) gap = 0.245; (b)+adv gap = 0.291. -> no.
3. **Frozen-LSA (b) trades all-users for within-archetype robustness?** (a) all-users 0.974 / within-arch 0.750; (b) all-users 0.958 / within-arch 0.850.

(CPU-reduced run: steps=1200, seeds=[0, 1]. Full spec = 15k steps x 3 seeds; rerun on GPU with default env for final numbers.)

